CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 3, 1962, pg. 10, reads: "Four Years Old! - Unlike adult women who find birthdays 'something not to shout about,' little Robin Bullard (center) was anxious to celebrate her fourth natal day. A group of her little friends joined in festivities at her grandmother's home, 2801 Bedford Ave. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Robin Bullard wearing ribbon corsage, seated behind sheet cake, for her fourth birthday, surrounded by other girls wearing party hats and boys, in home of Margaret Bullard, 2801 Bedford Avenue
